## LA Park won the match with interference from the debuting Perros del Mal, thus winning the rights to the name. After a musical performance, Marisela Pena announced the Mexico City commission had voided the finish due to the interference and so the name didn't change hands. (Few remember that part.) The two would rematch a month later in Merida where AAA's Parka won, but few remember that part too.

CMLL (FRI) 12/03/2010 Arena México [CMLL]
** Sin Piedad, 2010Attendance: 8400
1) Dark Angel, Luna Mágica, Marcela b Estrellita, Mima Shimoda, Tiffany
## Dark Angel replaced Goya Kong
2) Delta, Stuka Jr., Valiente b Euforia, Pólvora, Sangre Azteca
## Sangre Azteca had problems with Polvora at the end of their match.
3) Hijo del Fantasma, La Máscara, La Sombra DQ Averno, Ephesto, Mephisto
## Mephisto & Fantasma continued to feud. Tecnicos took the match in straight falls when Mephisto pulled Fantasma’s mask.
4) Eléctrico b Pequeño Warrior [mask]
## Electrico beat Warrior in about a 15 minute match, with a tapatia in the third. Pequeno Warrior was announced as Humberto Sanchez Medorio, same name he gave when he lost his mask as Mini Psicosis.
5) Latino, Místico, Shocker, Strong Man b Atlantis, Felino, Héctor Garza, Negro Casas
## Latin Lover’s new name is pronounced “Latin-OH.” He feuded with Garza & Tirantes in the semimain. Rudos were DQed for excessive violence in the first, then Latino pinned Garza in the second.
6) Rey Bucanero b Mr. Águila [hair]
## Mr. Aguila won the first fall of the main event with help from Tirantes. Rambo, at ringside as commission representative, removed Tirantes from the match. Babe Richard took over, and Bucanero won the second with a cradle and the third with a Canadian Destroyer (which Tirantes would’ve ruled a DQ.) No run ins, no interference.
